-- Deutsche Boerse, HSBC Holdings, Repsol: Europe Equity Preview
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-01-11T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/deutsche-boerse-hsbc-holdings-repsol-europe-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European (SXXP)  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  rose 1.8 percent to 250.82. The
 Stoxx 50 Index  gained 1.7 percent to 2,425.68. The  Euro Stoxx 50
Index , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro, increased
2.7 percent to 2,347.47.  Continental AG (CON)  (CON GY):  Europe ’s second-biggest
manufacturer of car parts said sales this year will rise as much
as 8 percent, helped by vehicle production growth in  Asia  and
 North America . Continental climbed 4.6 percent to 56.37 euros.  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  : The second-biggest Swiss
bank sold the unit handling backoffice processing for its U.S.
and  European (SXXP)  leveraged-loans business to outsourcing firm
UnitedLex for an undisclosed amount. Credit Suisse rose 2.5
percent to 21.52 francs.  Deutsche Boerse AG (DB1)  (DB1 GY): The chief executives of the
German stock exchange and NYSE Euronext will meet in New York to
discuss the European regulators’ opposition to their merger,
according to two people with direct knowledge of the matter.
 Deutsche Boerse  gained 4.9 percent to 42.02 euros.  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  : Europe’s largest bank by
market value named Jean Beunardeau as chief executive officer of
HSBC  France , replacing Christophe de Backer, who leaves after 21
years at the bank. HSBC rose 2.7 percent to 504.70 pence.  K+S AG (SDF)  (SDF GY): The world’s largest producer of salt
reiterated a forecast to sell about 14 million metric tons of
de-icing salt this year, after some countries in Europe
experienced warmer-than-average winter weather. K+S climbed 4.2
percent to 36.83 euros.  Repsol YPF SA (REP)  :  Spain ’s biggest oil company is
selling 61 million of its own shares, offloading half of the 10
percent stake it bought from Sacyr Vallehermoso SA (SYV SM) last
month to help the shareholder repay a loan. Repsol gained 1.2
percent to 23.54 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
